This paper discusses the development of a debugging approach for Inductive Logic Programming (ILP) algorithms, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and data mining (DB) applications. The paper also mentions the use of low-level implementation and the complexity of ILP problems, which are relevant to machine learning (LG) and software engineering (SE) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the delta debugging algorithm, which is a technique used in programming languages (PL) to automatically reduce the time needed to expose bugs.
